HEADWORD: Encapsulation
<hw>En*cap`su*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The act of inclosing in a capsule; the growth
of a membrane around (any part) so as to inclose it in a
capsule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Encarnalize</ent>⟦br⟧
